    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="36"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d36">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Council/4–846</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Soviet Foreign Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Molotov</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="67" xml:id="d36fn67">The original Russian text of this message was
                        transmitted to the Secretary of State on April 8, by the Soviet Ambassador,
                        Nikolai Vasilyevich Novikov.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>I agree with your proposal to call in Paris on April 25 a meeting of the Council
                    of the Ministers of Foreign Affairs who, in conformity with the understanding at
                    the Moscow Meeting, are connected with the preparation of peace treaties for the
                    forthcoming conference not later than May 1.</p>
                <p>From the Soviet side, instructions have already been sent to London to expedite
                    to the maximum degree the work of the Deputies on the draft peace treaties in
                    order that the questions which remain in disagreement may be considered at the
                    meeting of the Ministers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-06">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">April</hi> 6, 1946</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
